{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3559745,"name":"Matt","username":"romi_roams","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/779978/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-17T20:52:17.463Z","cooked":"<p>The <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/romi-robot/hardware-support.html" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">wpilib Romi page</a> says additional encoders (beyond the two built-in motor encoders) are incompatible. Just trying to understand why since I’m at the point of wanting to add motors/controllers for additional hardware like mini-elevator.</p>
<p>The 32U4 board has GPIO pins that can be configured for Digital I/O. Are they fundamentally different than the DIO pins dedicated to the motor encoders that are setup like this?</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">  // The Romi has onboard encoders that are hardcoded
  // to use DIO pins 4/5 and 6/7 for the left and right
  private final Encoder m_leftEncoder = new Encoder(4, 5);
  private final Encoder m_rightEncoder = new Encoder(6, 7);
</code></pre>
<p>Specifically, not sure why another identical encoder can’t be connected to EXT0 in this example config from the Romi section. If I had one I’d try it out but I don’t have an extra encoder.</p>
